==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bufflehead
<hw>Buf"fle*head`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Buffle</ets> + <ets>head</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who has a large head; a heavy, stupid fellow.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What makes you stare so, <qex>bufflehead</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Plautus (trans. 1694).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The buffel duck. See <er>Buffel
duck</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buffle-headed</ent>⟦br⟧
